WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good evening, Jacob. It's Wednesday, April fifteenth, twenty twenty-six. Welcome

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
to Nightcap — a new experiment. Think of this as

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
the other half of your morning briefing. Not what you

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
need to know, but what changed, what landed, and one

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
thing worth sitting with. Let's start with the scorecard. How

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
the numbers moved since this morning. The S and P

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
five hundred closed at a new all-time record today: seven

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
thousand, twenty-two point ninety-five. Up zero point eight percent. This

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
morning I told you it was zero point two percent

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
off the January record. Well, it blew past it. The

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
catalyst? Ceasefire optimism. Semafor's evening edition led with the headline

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
"Stronger than the narrative suggests." Investors are betting the blockade

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
resolves through negotiation, not escalation. Jefferson City warmed up from

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
sixty-six degrees this morning to seventy-three tonight. Storms are rolling

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
in after midnight — eighty percent chance — so close

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
your windows before bed. Tomorrow looks even better than we

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
predicted this morning: eighty-four degrees and becoming sunny. That's six

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
degrees hotter than the seventy-eight we had this morning. Great

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
driving weather for Columbia and Unbound. On prediction markets, the

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
"Anthropic releases a model above four point six by today"

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
market closed at zero point seven percent. No Opus four

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
point seven today. But the Claude five before July first

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
market sits at seventy-four percent, and Claude five Opus before

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
October first is at ninety-one percent. The release is coming

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
— just not yet. Iran markets held flat: retaliation by

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
July still at seventy-eight percent, Hormuz normal by April thirtieth

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
barely budged from seven to eight percent. Now, the plot

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
thickens. Stories from this morning that developed legs. The blockade

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
is now official. This morning I walked you through The

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Atlantic's analysis of how it works. Tonight it's confirmed: Admiral

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
Brad Cooper stated the blockade is, quote, fully implemented. But

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
it's messy. Iran claims four vessels still transited today. And

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
here's the escalation: Iran's joint military command threatened to completely

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
block all exports and imports across the Persian Gulf, Sea

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
of Oman, and Red Sea if the U-S doesn't lift

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
the blockade. The ceasefire lapses April twenty-first. Pakistan has a

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
negotiator in Tehran. The White House says it's optimistic about

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
a deal. Six days. Anthropic had a day. No Opus

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
four point seven drop — the Manifold market confirmed it.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
But Claude went down this morning. Service outage, login success

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
rates cratered, recovered around twelve thirty P-M Eastern. Your daily

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
driver had a bad morning. TechCrunch reports Anthropic is actively

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
shrugging off the eight hundred billion dollar valuation offers. They're

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
not in a rush to raise. Meanwhile, Glasswing got institutional

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
partners — Microsoft and J-P Morgan are officially in, with

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
up to a hundred million dollars in usage credits for

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
defensive vulnerability scanning. And Fortune ran a piece on the

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
wave of user backlash over Claude's perceived performance decline. The

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
community frustration is getting mainstream coverage now. Fresh intel. Things

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
that weren't on the radar this morning. The biggest story

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
of the day by raw internet attention: a jury ruled

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
that Live Nation and Ticketmaster operated as an illegal monopoly

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
and overcharged fans. Thirty-seven thousand upvotes on r-slash-technology. This is

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
the first step toward a potential breakup. Landmark consumer protection

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
moment. Trump threatened to fire Fed Chair Jerome Powell if

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
he doesn't resign. This has been a recurring threat, but

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
the timing — during a blockade-driven market rally — makes

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
it particularly destabilizing. In peak twenty twenty-six market absurdity, Allbirds

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
— the shoe company — announced a pivot to A-I,

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
and their stock exploded three hundred percent. Almost two thousand

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
Reddit comments, mostly bewildered. Iran bought a Chinese satellite to

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
target U-S military sites in the Middle East. The purchase

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
agreement included ongoing ground control services based in China. The

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
China-Iran axis is deeper than just oil. And quietly, Nature

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
reports that a method to reverse cellular aging is about

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
to be tested in humans. File this under things that

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
will matter more than anything else we talked about today,

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
if it works. Your day in receipts. The financial snapshot.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
You ordered a book from Amazon this afternoon — "Simplify:

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
Do Fifty Percent." Your Walgreens photo order is ready for

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
pickup after an earlier delay. An Apple Card payment of

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
thirty-four ninety-five nineteen was received — that's a significant chunk.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
Tax Day payoff? And you got a receipt from Anthropic,

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
P-B-C for your monthly Claude subscription. You're simultaneously a customer,

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
an applicant, and a market analyst for the same company.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
That's a strange and interesting position to be in. Messages

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
tonight. Someone at a five-seven-three number texted: "I think we're

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
going to go to forty-four Canteen Friday if you're interested."

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Friday dinner invite. You'll be at Mom and Dad's for

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
Unbound — could work depending on timing. Dustin sent a

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
G-I-F. Walgreens confirmed your photo pickup. And from this morning

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
— Katelyn's seven photos are still unanswered if you haven't

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
replied yet. The feed tonight. Every newsletter ran "Mini-Vibe Check:

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
Claude Managed Agents Handle the Infrastructure Work" alongside a piece

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
making the case against L-L-Ms. Semafor Technology covered tokens becoming

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
central to A-I conversations. Your Readwise daily summary surfaced three

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
saved articles from yesterday. Polymarket's newsletter led with "Dems Surging."

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
And on Reddit, someone used Claude Cowork to find a

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
London flat in five days, a design system extractor plugin

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
hit four hundred upvotes, and the Claude A-I subreddit is

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
split between memes and genuine existential reflection about what A-I

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
coding is doing to the profession. One post in particular

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
is worth sitting with. A senior telecom engineer wrote: "Code

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
used to be expensive. It gave you a surface area

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
to sense when a pattern was pushing back on you."

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
He's talking about something bigger than code. Writing is expensive.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
Thinking is expensive. The friction is where the insight lives.

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
The morning briefing you listened to today? I wrote it.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
But the thinking about what matters — the editorial judgment,

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
the connections, the priorities — that's the part that can't

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
be automated away. Project Arete is about building things. But

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
the reason to build is the thinking the building forces.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
Tomorrow setup. Eighty-four degrees and sunny. Unbound Book Festival begins.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
Tonight is your last chance to finalize which panels you

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
care about. Terry Tempest Williams is keynoting. The arXiv evaluation

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
is due the day after tomorrow. And if you go

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
early, tomorrow morning is good running weather. Molly's Miles is

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
in ten days. Day three. Close the windows before the

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
storms. Pick your Unbound panels. Reply to Katelyn. Good night,

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:16.400
Jacob.
